## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{2x^3-5x^2+x}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(2x^2-5x+1)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=2x^2-5x+1
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{x^2+2x}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(x+2)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=x+2
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{3x^4-6x^2-x}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(3x^3-6x-1)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=3x^3-6x-1
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{2x^4-3x}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(2x^3-3)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=2x^3-3
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{x^5-3x^2+2x}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(x^4-3x+2)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=x^4-3x+2
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{3x^5-x}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(3x^4-1)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=3x^4-1
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{x^4+5x^3+3x^2}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(x^3+5x^2+3x)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=x^3+5x^2+3x
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{2x^4+4x^3-x^2}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(2x^3+4x^2-x)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=2x^3+4x^2-x
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{4x^3+x^2}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(4x^2+x)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=4x^2+x
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{x^3-5x^2}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(x^2-5x)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=x^2-5x
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{2x^5+5x^3}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(2x^4+5x^2)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=2x^4+5x^2
\end{align}$

## Canceling common factors

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{3x^5+x^4-4x^2}{x}&=\dfrac{\cancel{x}(3x^4+x^3-4x)}{\cancel{x}}
\\\\
&=3x^4+x^3-4x
\end{align}$
